      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "A comprehensive qualitative assessment of user-induced error sources was conducted by the simulation team lead and independently reviewed by a senior CFD analyst with 12 years of cardiovascular device experience. Boundary condition setup, material property assignment, and post-processing scripts were reviewed against a pre-approved simulation plan. All deviations from the plan were documented and adjudicated. The review panel concluded that the risk of consequential use error is low given the structured review process, the use of templated case setup files, and cross-verification of key inputs against the experimental test protocol. No structured gradation levels are defined for this factor under the applicable MRL 2 profile; the qualitative evidence collected is considered sufficient to support the overall Accepted determination.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of simulation setup, boundary conditions, and post-processing confirmed against pre-approved simulation plan with all deviations documented."
